      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Crumble your<strong> goats' cheese </strong>into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your<strong> cider vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and toss – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
